            <person xml:id="pers1700">
               <p><persName>Relly</persName> (also spelled &apos;<persName>Reily</persName>&apos;
                  and &apos;<persName>Reilly</persName>&apos;) was a Welsh cow farrier, who was
                  converted under <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers2221.xml"
                     />Whitefield</persName>&apos;s preaching in <date when="1743">1743</date>. He
                  became a Calvinistic Methodist minister, published a hymnbook and a treatise on
                     <hi rend="italic">The Union of Christ and His Church</hi> (<date when="1759"
                     >1759</date>) which <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers2180.xml"
                     />JW</persName> judged to affirm antinomianism. See <hi rend="italic">DEB</hi>,
                  925.</p>
            </person>
